
@startuml
' Class Diagram for School System

class School {
  -name: String
  -principal: Teacher
  +getPrincipal(): Teacher
}

class Teacher {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
  -email: String
  +teachesAt(school: School, hours: Integer): void
}

class Student {
  -firstName: String
  -lastName: String
  -school: School
  -classGroup: ClassGroup
  +enrollInClass(classGroup: ClassGroup): void
}

class ClassGroup {
  -name: String
  -students: List<Student>
  -classroom: Classroom
  +assignToClassroom(classroom: Classroom): void
}

class Room {
  -name: String
}

class Classroom extends Room {
  -capacity: Integer
}

class OtherRoom extends Room {
  -size: Integer
}

class TeachingAssignment {
  -teacher: Teacher
  -school: School
  -hours: Integer
}

class Principal {
  -teacher: Teacher
  -school: School
}

' Relationships

School "1" -- "1" Principal : has
Teacher "1" -- "*" TeachingAssignment : teaches at
Student "1" -- "1" School : attends
Student "1" -- "1" ClassGroup : belongs to
ClassGroup "1" -- "1" Classroom : assigned to
ClassGroup "1" -- "*" Student : contains
School "1" -- "*" Teacher : employs
Teacher "1" -- "*" TeachingAssignment : has assignments
Teacher "1" -- "0..1" Principal : is principal of
Room "1" -- "*" Classroom : extends
Room "1" -- "*" OtherRoom : extends
@enduml

### Explanation of Key Points:
- **School** has a **Principal**, who is one of the **Teachers**.
- A **Teacher** can teach at up to **three schools**, with each teaching relationship having a number of **hours** (modeled via `TeachingAssignment`).
- A **Student** is in exactly one **School** and one **ClassGroup**.
- A **ClassGroup** has a name and is assigned to one **Classroom** (a type of **Room**).
- **Rooms** are either **Classrooms** (with capacity) or **OtherRooms** (with size in square meters).

